                            <comment id="12893659" author="mradiguet" created="Thu, 29 Jul 2010 15:30:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Java class used for tests &amp;amp; pdf file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12980668" author="mradiguet" created="Wed, 12 Jan 2011 11:14:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is still present in pdfbox 1.4.0 . You can reproduce the problem with fileSizeIssue.zip.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13818828" author="mhilpert" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 10:15:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My tests with PDFBox 1.8.2:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;addPage(): inly a few KB smaller PDF (for PDFs that have multiple megabytes)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;importPage(): results in PDFs upt to 3 times bigger than the original PDF!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Both remove the outlines from th original PDF, so this alone is a show stopper.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14245308" author="tilman" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2014 12:40:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;java -jar pdfbox-app-2.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar PDFSplit -endPage 2300 Default_Table_Formatting-merged.pdf&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;brings a result file with size 36MB &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The content stream is not compressed.  Is there a reason that PDDocument.importPage() does not use compression for the content stream? With compression (adding dest.addCompression(); ), I get a size of 15MB.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14245311" author="lehmi" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2014 12:50:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Adding compression is one of the ideas I saw somewhere in one of the related tickets. And yes, I&apos;m going to add that. Another approach is to remove all annotations as well, as those will most likely become invalid&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14255205" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2014 16:43:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1647167 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1647167&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1647167&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-785&quot; title=&quot;Spliting a PDF creates unnecessarily large files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: add compression to stream when importing an existing page as proposed by Thomas S&#246;rensen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14255207" author="jira-bot" created="Sun, 21 Dec 2014 16:45:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1647169 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1647169&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1647169&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-785&quot; title=&quot;Spliting a PDF creates unnecessarily large files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: add compression to stream when importing an existing page as proposed by Thomas S&#246;rensen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14255612" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 22 Dec 2014 10:26:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1647281 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1647281&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1647281&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-785&quot; title=&quot;Spliting a PDF creates unnecessarily large files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: remove all pages within annotations to avoid the import of unneeded resources&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14255615" author="jira-bot" created="Mon, 22 Dec 2014 10:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1647283 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=lehmi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;lehmi&quot;&gt;lehmi&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/1.8&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1647283&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1647283&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-785&quot; title=&quot;Spliting a PDF creates unnecessarily large files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-785&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-785&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: remove all pages within annotations to avoid the import of unneeded resources&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14255621" author="lehmi" created="Mon, 22 Dec 2014 10:35:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve followed 2 of the obvious proposals:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add compression to the stream of the imported pages&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;remove all pages from annotation links to avoid copying of unneeded resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks to all for their input/help/contribution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276168" author="bpreindl" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 09:53:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In Version 1.8.12, this issue still exists. If I split a PDF which contains scanned images (one on each page) having 6MB in overall size, I get &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;number of pages&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; PDF files having 6MB as well. So each single PDF page contains all resources of all pages, obviously. When re-merging all pages to one PDF file, the PDF file (and this is our main issue) becomes &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;number of pages&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; multiplied by the original document size. So a 6MB PDF file with 10 pages becomes a 60MB PDF file when being split and re-merged.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276170" author="tilman" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 09:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a different problem than in this issue and you described it yourself, that if one page contains all the resources of all pages. To solve this, we would have to run a complex test (that can be recursive, because some resources can have content streams and resources too) to check which resources are really used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276182" author="bpreindl" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 10:08:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would it make sense to issue this as a new bug? Or is it no bug in general but rather an optimization? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think I understand the issue: All pages of a PDF contain all resources of the PDF when they are added to another PDF because it&apos;s a complex problem to identify which resources belong to which page, right? And when multiple single PDFs are merged together, all resources from all PDFs are also merged together (which makes absolutely sense).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Have you already tried to find a solution respectively are you working on this or is it sensible if we try to fix it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15276197" author="tilman" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 10:25:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes you understood the problem correctly. However the check must be made both for page level and global resources or mid-level-page-tree resources. And in theory, there could be unneeded resources deeper, i.e. below page level.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes it is rather an optimization and not a bug. You can open an issue but this doesn&apos;t mean it will be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nobody is working on that topic. I don&apos;t think people will... there are so many other problems. If you want to work on this yourself, have a look at ExtractImages.java.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
